@inproceedings{Chen2014The,
    abstract = {{Aim: With the Apps being more popular around the world, augmentative and alternative communication (AAC) apps also becomes an option for people with complex communication disabilities. However, the small icon might make the pointing task more difficult on the small device. This study aimed to explore how the size of icon affects the performance of the pointing icons on the smart phone. Methods: Four children with intellectual disabilities were recruited to participate in a repeated measurement experiment. All the participated children were identified by the local education agent. Two factors design, operating method (one hand and two hands) and size of icon (3*5, 4*6, and 5*7), was adopted in this study. Accuracy and speed were used as indicators to represent the performance. Results: The results indicated that the accurate rates were higher when operating in two hands even in executing the tasks with smaller icons. However, the speed of pointing the target icon correctly was not significant difference between operating methods. One the other hand, generally, bigger icon gained higher accuracy and speed. Conclusion: The popular AAC app in typical handheld multi touch device usually adopt grilled layout design. Size of icons is one of the major considerations for designing layout. The results indicated that with the size decreased, the accuracy and speed decreased. Meanwhile two hands operating method could help the children with intellectual disabilities to perform higher accuracy.}},
